article.description: — Frankie Policelli made four 3-pointers and scored a career-high 22 points as Stony Brook narrowly beat Ivy League favorite Yale 85-81 on Sunday.
article.headline: Policelli scores 22 to lead Stony Brook over Yale 85-81
article.linkText: Policelli scores 22 to lead Stony Brook over Yale 85-81
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. -- — Frankie Policelli made four 3-pointers and scored a career-high 22 points as Stony Brook narrowly beat Ivy League favorite Yale 85-81 on Sunday. Anthony Roberts had 19 points and six rebounds for Stony Brook (2-3). Tykei Greene added 11 points and six rebounds. Tyler Stephenson-Moore and Juan Felix Rodriguez each had 10 points. Azar Swain had 22 points for the Bulldogs (4-4). Matthue Cotton added 17 points and seven rebounds. Jalen Gabbidon had 14 points. E.J. Jarvis scored 13 with eight rebounds and Eze Dike scored 10. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
